      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"tough on crime\" laws are a double-edged sword that often fail to reduce crime while disproportionately harming marginalized communities. Research consistently shows that these policies, which focus on punitive measures like longer prison sentences and mandatory minimums, do not effectively deter criminal behavior and instead create a cycle of incarceration that harms families and neighborhoods. Instead of relying on such harsh legislation, cities should invest in proven community-based strategies like affordable housing, mental health support, and restorative justice programs to truly keep their streets safe.",
