    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the sociological side of it, but what about the people who think that strict sentencing is the only thing keeping violent crime in check? like, isn't there some merit to the idea that if people know the consequences are heavy, they'll think twice before committing a crime? it feels like you're kind of dismissing the deterrence argument entirely.",
