      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but you keep saying \"the real issue\" is a lack of alternatives, like it's a settled fact. isn't it also true that some people just believe that law and order is a necessary foundation for any society to function? it seems like you're framing the punitive approach as just a \"failure\" while treating the social support model as the \"effective\" one, but isn't that just one way of looking at it?",
